Public Interfaces:

Dalsgaard, P., Halskov, K. (2012). Designing urban media facades: cases and challenges. Prof. of CHI, ACM.

Jennifer G. Sheridan, Nick Bryan-Kinns. (2008). Designing for Performative Tangible Interaction. Int. J. Arts and Technology. Vol. 1, Nos. 3/4, 2008

Seitinger, S., et al. (2009). Urban pixels: painting the city with light. Proc. of CHI, ACM, 839 - 848.

Seitinger, S., et al. (2010). Light bodies: exploring interactions with responcive lights. Proc. of TEI, ACM, 113 -120


Prototyping:

Steve Hodges, Stuart Taylor, Niclas Villar, James Scott, and John Helmes, 2013. Exporing physical prototyping techniques for functional devices using-NET gadgeteer. In Proceedings of the 7th International Conference on Tangible, Embedded and Embodied Interaction (TEI '13). ACM, New York, NY, USA, 271-274

Archtecture & Urbanism:

Gehl Archtects. Places for People. Melbourne 2004.

Tuck W. Leong and Martin Brynskov. 2009. CO_2nfession: engaging with values through urban conversations. In Proceedings of the 21st Annual Conderence of the Australian Computer-Human Interaction Special Interest Group: Design: Open 24/7 (OZCHI '09). ACM, New York, NY, USE, 209-216.

Hendrik Korsgaard, Nicolas Brodersen Hansen, Ditte Basballe, Peter Dasgaard, and Kim Halskov. 2012. Odenplan: a media facade design process. In Proceedings of the 4th Meia Architecture Biennale Conference: Participation (MAB '12).


Mobile:

Jens Grubert, Ann Morrison, Helmut Munz, and gerhard Reitmayr. 2012. Playing it real: magic lens and static peephole interfaces for gaes in a public space. In Proceedings of the 14th international conference on Human-computer interaction with mobile device and services (MobileHCI '12). ACM, New York, NY, USA, 231-240.

Internet of Thinks:

Hodges, S., et al. Prototyping Connected Devices for the Internet of Things. IEEE, 2013.
